<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 4: CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - DRAINING
        THE SUPPLY MANIFOLD
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DRAINING THE SUPPLY MANIFOLD</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>THE SUPPLY MANIFOLD OIL RAIL MUST BE DRAINED PRIOR TO REMOVING THE FUEL INJECTORS TO PREVENT
                    LEAKAGE INTO THE CYLINDER BORE.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Use the following steps to remove the supply manifold end plug.</para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
            <title>DRAIN THE SUPPLY MANIFOLD</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the supply manifold by removing the supply manifold end plug from the supply
                    manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600410">4.10</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Be sure to clean any and all old Loctite(r) found on the threads of the plug prior to
                            installation.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-Ring and back-up ring onto the end plug (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600411">4.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply Loctite(r) #277 to the end plug threads and install into the supply manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600411">4.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ). Tighten plug to the special torque value (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600412">4.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600410" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5130" filename="../figeg5/EG5130.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.10 Removing Supply Manifold End Plug</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600411" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5132" filename="../figeg5/EG5132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.11 End Plug O-Ring And Back-Up Ring Locations</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. End Plug</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Back-up Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. O-Ring</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600412" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5131" filename="../figeg5/EG5131.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.12 Installing Supply Manifold End Plug</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
